Strange question, but I attended a workshop where the facilitator asked the participants to think about &quot;What&#x27;s the best place you ever worked and why?&quot;. It struck me as something I&#x27;ve only implicitly pondered, and never explicitly. I was wondering if people had other questions that helped them reflect on their careers.<p>&quot;What do you think makes a good programmer?&quot;
&quot;Who is the strongest engineer you know and what makes them that way?&quot;
&quot;What thing or things are stopping you from achieving the thing you want to achieve?&quot;
